This paper deals with Bayesian agents learning from private signals and the actions of others, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of increased interaction on learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the concept of consensus and information theory, which are relevant to social networks and information theory (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively.
